# 1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)

---

# 🔹 What is ISA?

ISA (Instruction Set Architecture) defines:

* Instructions
* Registers
* Addressing modes
* Data types

Based on ISA design philosophy:

👉 Architectures are mainly classified into:

* RISC
* CISC

---

# 🔹 RISC (Reduced Instruction Set Computer)

Goal:
👉 Simpler instructions
👉 Faster execution

---

## 🔹 Main Features of RISC

### 1️⃣ Simple Instructions

* Small instruction set
* Simple operations

---

### 2️⃣ Fixed Instruction Length

Example:

* 32-bit instructions

📌 Easier decoding.

---

### 3️⃣ Few Addressing Modes

Simplifies hardware.

---

### 4️⃣ Load-Store Architecture

Only:

* LOAD
* STORE

access memory.

All other operations use registers.

---

### 5️⃣ More Registers

Large register set improves speed.

---

### 6️⃣ Pipeline Friendly

Simple instructions improve pipelining.

---

# 🔹 Examples of RISC

* ARM
* MIPS
* SPARC
* RISC-V

---

# 🔹 CISC (Complex Instruction Set Computer)

Goal:
👉 Reduce number of instructions per program.

---

## 🔹 Main Features of CISC

### 1️⃣ Complex Instructions

One instruction may perform multiple tasks.

---

### 2️⃣ Variable Instruction Length

Different instruction sizes.

📌 Decoding becomes complex.

---

### 3️⃣ Many Addressing Modes

More flexibility.

---

### 4️⃣ Memory-to-Memory Operations

Operations can directly access memory.

---

### 5️⃣ Fewer Registers

More memory dependence.

---

### 6️⃣ Complex Control Unit

Often microprogrammed.

---

# 🔹 Examples of CISC

* x86
* Intel processors

---

# 🔹 RISC vs CISC Comparison

| Feature            | RISC    | CISC     |
| ------------------ | ------- | -------- |
| Instruction Set    | Small   | Large    |
| Instruction Length | Fixed   | Variable |
| Addressing Modes   | Few     | Many     |
| Execution          | Faster  | Slower   |
| Hardware           | Simpler | Complex  |
| Registers          | More    | Fewer    |
| Pipelining         | Easier  | Harder   |

---

# 🔹 Important GATE Concepts

---

## 🔹 CPI (Cycles Per Instruction)

RISC:

* Lower CPI

CISC:

* Higher CPI but fewer instructions.

---

## 🔹 Compiler Role

RISC relies more on:
👉 Efficient compiler optimization.

---

# 🔹 Common GATE Traps

* Thinking RISC means fewer instructions in program ❌
* Confusing instruction count with instruction complexity
* Forgetting load-store property

